# NOTE: GitHub Pages IGNORES this file. It only applies if you deploy the same
# static folder to Cloudflare Pages (or another host that reads _headers).
# On GitHub Pages, rely on <meta charset="UTF-8"> early in <head> — see docs/CHARSET-UTF8.md
#
# Tell browsers and proxies these files are UTF-8. Without this, some hosts serve
# text/html without charset; the browser may use Windows-1252/Latin-1 and show
# mojibake (e.g. "whatÃ¢â¬â¢s" instead of "what's", "â¢" instead of "™").
# Cloudflare Pages: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/

/*.html
  Content-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8

/*.json
  Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8

/data/*
  Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8

/*.css
  Content-Type: text/css; charset=utf-8

/*.js
  Content-Type: application/javascript; charset=utf-8
